ipeline to sample and measure stellar magnitudes and positions\naround the cluster candidates using DAOPHOT. We also implement a\nmaximum-likelihood method to fit individual density profiles and\ncolour-magnitude diagrams. For 117 (from a total of 255) of the cluster\ncandidates (28 uncatalogued clusters), we obtain reliable ages, metallicities,\ndistance moduli and structural parameters, confirming their nature as physical\nsystems. The distribution of cluster metallicities shows a radial dependence,\nwith no clusters more metal-rich than [Fe/H] ~ -0.7 beyond 8 kpc from the LMC\ncenter. The age distribution has two peaks at ~ 1.2 Gyr and ~ 2.7 Gyr.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 3 Dec 2015 11:00:09 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-07-27"}
